<section id="feature2">
    <h3>
        Brand UCosmic with my own organization's look and feel
    </h3>
    <p>
        <strong>In order to</strong> provide a coherent user interface for people using
        my organization's web sites,
        <br />
        <strong>As an</strong> international office,
        <br />
        <strong>I want to</strong> apply custom branding to the UCosmic design and layout
        (look &amp; feel).
    </p>
    <p>
        UC isn't the only consortium member to receive a custom look and feel in the above
        screenshots. In addition to the default layout, we've also created custom layouts
        for each of the consortium members who have been participating in the preview. You
        can see what the different layouts look like by opening <a href="@Url.Action(MVC.Common.Skins.Sample())" target="_blank">
            this page</a>. If you would like us to create a &quot;skin&quot; for your organization,
        <a href="https://ucosmic.uservoice.com" target="_blank">drop us a line in the feedback
            forum</a>.
    </p>
    <p>
        When users sign on, the look and feel is automatically applied. You can also apply
        the look and feel using a URL when linking to UCosmic from your internal web sites.
        Here is an example link for the University of Minnesota:
    </p>
    <p>
        <a href="https://preview.ucosmic.com/as/www.umn.edu?returnUrl=/my/institutional-agreements"
            target="_blank">https://preview.ucosmic.com/as/www.umn.edu?returnUrl=/my/institutional-agreements</a>
    </p>
    <hr />
</section>
